OL,3,GCentral, Tayside & Fife
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA cloudy day with outbreaks of
OL,6,Fshowery rain in the north in the
OL,7,Fmorning but drier elsewhere. A drier
OL,8,Fafternoon with some bright spells, but
OL,9,Fstill the odd shower possible for all
OL,10,Fparts, which may be heavy. Light winds.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FA mostly cloudy and dry
OL,13,Fevening but with the odd isolated
OL,14,Fshower possible. Cloudy overnight with
OL,15,Fany showers becoming confined to
OL,16,Fwestern Tayside and Central areas.
OL,17,
OL,18,CTuesday:FA cloudy start with showers
OL,19,Fin the west. Showers soon clearing and
OL,20,Fcloud breaking up to give long sunny
OL,21,Fperiods through the afternoon.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
